headline: Autodesk Had an ‘Uneventful’ Quarter. The Stock Is Surging Anyway.
summary: Autodesk’s  rock-solid quarter was just what investors seem to have wanted to see.  Autodesk posted adjusted earnings of $2.67 a share for the quarter, ahead of analysts’ consensus call for $2.50, according to FactSet.  Autodesk shares jumped 7.9% to $317.63 in premarket trading Wednesday.

headline: ADSK Q3 2025 Deep Dive: AI, Cloud, and Platform Expansion Drive Outperformance
summary: 3D design software company Autodesk (NASDAQ:ADSK) reported revenue ahead of Wall Streets expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 18% year on year to $1.85 billion. Guidance for next quarter’s revenue was optimistic at $1.91 billion at the midpoint, 2.6% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.67 per share was 6.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
